Shell moderately keeled, with numerous tiny tubercles on shell surface (
Fig. 4B
). Flagellum like a short protrusion with a pointed tip, penis swollen, base of gametolytic sac narrow. Radula with slender, lanceolate central teeth.

SHELL (
Fig. 3B
, 
Table 1
). Dextral, medium-sized, tightly coiled, with 6½ slightly convex whorls. Suture rather shallow, apex obtuse with high conical spire. Body whorl angular, with tubercles all over its surface, without distinct incised spiral lines. Colour red brown in living specimens (
Fig. 4B
), empty shells are paler (
Fig. 3B
). Umbilicus deep and wide. Aperture obliquely oval, reflexed, and slightly thickened.

RADULA (n = 3). Comprises 126–130 transverse rows with 79–87 teeth per row; radular formula: (28– 30)-(11–13)-1-(11–13)-(28–30). Central tooth symmetric, slender lanceolate, and unicuspid (
Fig. 6D
). Lateral teeth larger than the central tooth, lanceolate, bicuspid, with large endocone and sharp cusp (
Fig. 6D
). Marginal teeth tricuspid, with small sharp endocone; large, slender mesocone; and small v-shaped ectocone with two cusps (
Fig. 6E–F
).
